Package: sessioncleanr
Type: Package
Title: Conservative End-of-Session Cleanup Utilities
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Thierry", family = "Warin", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "thierry.warin@example.com"))
Description: Provides a single high-level function 'clean_session()' to close graphics devices, stop parallel clusters, close connections, disconnect DBI connections, clear temporary files created in the current tempdir, optionally unload non-base namespaces, remove objects from the global environment, and trigger garbage collection. Designed to be called at the end of scripts and in 'on.exit()' handlers.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports: DBI, parallel
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
